The Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize announced that the total number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in South Africa is 5951 as at Friday, 1 May. This is an increase of 304 confirmed cases from the previous days report. Recoveries as at 29 April is 2382
The total number of tests conducted to date is 217 522, of which 9 992 were done in the last 24 hours. 
Deaths: 13 new deaths. Total deaths = 116 (W/Cape, Gauteng, KZN and E/Cape)
